    "comment": "Rationale: protein tyrosine phosphatase-interacting protein 51 (PTPIP51, gene RMDN3) is a known mitochondrial membrane protein (PMID:26899735).\n\nFigure 1: SIM super-resolution microscopy of cultured rat hippocampal neurons showed PTPIP51 localized to the presynaptic compartment (identified by immunostaining for axons with phosphorylated NFH and synaptophysin).\n\nFigure 1e: VAPB and PTPIP51 are present in synaptoneurosome biochemical fractions prepared from rat brain.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Hippocampal neurons were obtained from embryonic day 18 rat embryos and cultured in Neurobasal medium ...\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Rabbit and rat antibodies to VAPB and PTPIP51 were as described [9]. PMID:22131369\nRabbit anti-PTPIP51 and chicken anti-MAP 2 were from Gentex.\"",
